Bret Treadway was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas and was pronounced deceased at 9:52 p.m.

	The driver of the Buick stopped and stayed on scene. No charges are expected at this time.

	The case is still being investigated.

The preliminary investigation shows that a black, Harley Davidson motorcycle, was northbound, inside lane, near the 7700 block of Decker Lane. An orange Harley Davidson was also traveling northbound and slowed to make a U-turn. The black motorcycle struck the orange motorcycle from behind.

	The driver of the black motorcycle was taken to the hospital with non-life threatening injuries. His passenger, identified as Cheryl Kelly, 56, was transported to Dell Seton with critical injuries. Kelly succumbed to her injuries June 12, 2018, and was pronounced deceased at 3:43 p.m.

	Alcohol was not considered a factor in the collision. This is Austin’s 28th fatal traffic crash of 2018, resulting in 29 fatalities this year. At this time in 2017, there were 29 fatal traffic crashes and 31 traffic fatalities.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2003 Ford Ranger, traveling eastbound, was crossing an icy bridge, in the 1500 block of W. Slaughter Lane. The driver, identified as 59-year-old Kenneth Odeal Craig, lost control from the middle lane and veered to his right, resulting in the vehicle jumping over the south curb and rolling over a guardrail/chain link fence, falling 30 feet to the ground.
At 5:36 p.m., passenger Eva Marie Gonzales was pronounced deceased at the scene. The driver was taken to St. David's South Austin Medical Center with life threatening injuries.
	This case is still being investigated.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2011 Harley Davidson motorcycle stopped facing westbound in the 7300 block of Decker Lane. A tan, 2011, Buick Lacrosse was traveling northbound in the 7300 block of Decker Lane when it struck the motorcycle. The driver of the motorcycle, Mark Capistran, was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas with life-threatening injuries. He passed away on Monday, June 11, 2018 at 1:21 p.m.

	The driver of the Buick stopped and stayed on scene. No charges are expected at this time.

	The case is still being investigated.

location: E US 290 and Harris Branch Parkway
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that a black, 2004 Infiniti G35 traveling northbound on Harris Branch Parkway collided with a white, 18-wheeler on the westbound 290 frontage road. The crash occurred in an intersection controlled by a traffic light. The male driving the G35 died at the scene while the driver of the 18-wheeler was transported with non-life threatening injuries.

	The case is still being investigated.

location: Intersection of Springdale Road and Webberville Road
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that Michael Watson lost control of the black, 2018 Indian motorcycle he was driving northbound, on Springdale Road. He struck the west curb of Springdale Road before hitting the north curb on Webberville Road and then crashed into a utility pole. Watson was thrown from the motorcycle.

	He was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas, but succumbed to his injuries and was pronounced deceased at 11:22 a.m. on Wednesday, June 20, 2018.

The preliminary investigation shows that a blue 2009 Honda Civic was traveling eastbound on W. Cesar Chavez St. A black 2015 Ford F150 truck was traveling westbound on W. Cesar Chavez. The Honda Civic lost control in the 1500 block and veered into the path of the Ford F150.

	The driver of the Honda Civic, Pinkeshkumar Dineshbhai Patel, was pronounced dead at the scene.

	The driver of the Ford F150 was trasported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas with minor injuries.

The preliminary investigation shows that a silver, 1997 Toyota 4Runner was traveling westbound in the outside lane of traffic in the 800 block of Rutland Dr.

	A pedestrian, identified as Troy Dean Fisher, was attempting to cross Rutland Drive north curb southbound to the south curb. He was not in the crosswalk and was struck by the Toyota 4Runner.

	Troy Dean Fisher was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas and was pronounced deceased at 9:38 p.m.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2005 white Infinity and a white 2015 International pulling a white 2006 trailer were traveling southbound on N IH 35 in the lower deck. The Infinity failed to maintain an assured clear distance and struck the trailer.

	The driver of the Infinity was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas where he died as a result of his injuries on Monday, July 23, 2018.

	No charges are expected against the driver of the trailer.

The preliminary investigation shows that a pedestrian was walking eastbound on the south curb line of the 5700 block of Parmer Lane when an unknown vehicle, also traveling eastbound, struck him. It is unknown if the pedestrian was walking in the bicycle lane or the grassy shoulder when he was struck.

	The vehicle that struck the pedestrian fled the scene and remains unidentified. The pedestrian, identified as Scott Gerald Whiting, died on scene.

The preliminary investigation shows that a white 1989 Honda motorcycle was traveling southbound on Bluff Springs Road when a blue 2012 Toyota Prius turned in front of it. The Prius was traveling northbound on Bluff Springs Road and attempting to turn left into the convenience store parking lot located in the 7600 block. The driver of the motorcycle was transported to St. David’s South Austin Hospital where he died as a result of his injuries.

	The driver of the motorcycle, Brandon Thomas Buentello, was transported to St. David’s South Austin Hospital where he later died as a result of his injuries.

	No charges are pending against the driver of the Prius.

location: 1100 block E. Anderson Ln. westbound service road
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that a pedestrian was walking eastbound on the side walk along the north curb line of E. Anderson Ln. A 2018 black Mitsubishi Mirage was traveling westbound on E. Anderson Ln. when the driver of the vehicle lost control. The vehicle jumped the curb and struck the pedestrian with its right front.

	The pedestrian was transported to Dell Seton Medical center, and was later identified as Luis Cristobal Landeros. Mr. Landeros succumbed to his injuries shortly after and was pronounced deceased at 9:19 a.m.

The preliminary investigation shows that a pedestrian was walking westbound across the 500 block of N IH 35 proper. The pedestrian was then struck by a 2007 green Mack truck tractor that was traveling southbound in the outside lane.

	The pedestrian, identified as David O’Berine, was pronounced deceased at the scene.

The preliminary investigation shows that a pedestrian was standing in the southbound lane of traffic in the 11600 block of Manchaca Rd. when he was struck by a 2005 white Chevorlet pickup traveling southbound in the same lane.

	The pedestrian, identified as Tennie Ross, and was pronounced deceased at the scene.

Both the suspect vehicle and suspect are now in the Austin Police Department's (APD) custody from yesterday's fatal crash incident that occurred in the 600 block of W. Ben White. Suspect Darrell Smitty, 52, booking photo is pictured below. He's being charged with failure to stop and render aid. 
	Note: Booking photo is from a 2016 arrest. 


	The preliminary investigation shows that a pedestrian, identified as 40-year-old Ernesto Garcia, was walking westbound near a bus stop in the 600 block of W. Ben White Service Road. The suspect driver was westbound on the service road in the right turn lane. The suspect drove straight through the intersection, onto the sidewalk, between the bus stop and a Capital Metro bus that had stopped to pick up passengers, striking the pedestrian. 
	Ernesto Garcia was pronounced deceased at the scene. 
	The truck came to a stop in a driveway the driver walked to where Garcia lay, then walked back to his truck and drove away. 
	This is Austin's 39th fatal traffic crash and 40th traffic fatality of 2018. At this time in 2017, there were 34 fatal traffic crashes and 26 traffic fatalities. This case is still being investigated.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2005 Honda motorcycle was traveling northbound on Vintage Hills Dr. when the driver lost control and struck a dumpster. The driver of the motorcycle was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas where he was pronounced deceased at 7:48 p.m.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2018, silver Mitsubishi was traveling northbound in the 6900 block of Guadalupe Street when the driver collided with a pedestrian, Thomas Edward Craig, just north of the Kenniston Drive intersection. Mr. Craig was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas – Seton Healthcare where he succumbed to his injuries on August 24, 2018. The driver of the vehicle remained on scene.

The preliminary investigation shows that a white, 2012 Infinity was traveling northbound at high rate of speed in the 12000 block of N. IH-35 service rd. It left the roadway for unknown reasons, causing the vehicle to flip several times. The driver and lone occupant of the vehicle was transported to Round Rock Hospital where she died as a result of her injuries.

Arrested:      Felipe Hernandez, Hispanic male (21 years of age)

	The preliminary investigation shows that a pedestrian ran into the roadway after being asked if she could run fast in high heels. A 2007, maroon, GMC Yukon, traveling southbound on the frontage rd. of IH 35, approaching 7th St. struck the pedestrian, in the left lane. The Yukon left the scene but returned a short time later. The pedestrian was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas for emergency medical care. Officers arrested the driver of the Yukon and charged him with fail to stop and render aid.

	The pedestrian, Deemora Benson, died as a result of her injuries on Sunday, September 2, 2018.

The preliminary investigation shows that a white, 2004 Chevrolet Trailblazer was traveling northbound in the 10700 block of N. IH-35 when the vehicle left the roadway for unknown reasons and began to roll. The driver, Kendall Taylor Dezelle, and her passenger were ejected. They were both transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas – Seton Healthcare where the driver died on August 27, 2018.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2012 Hyundai was traveling southbound in the 500 block of S. Pleasant Valley Rd. when it crossed the center yellow line and into the northbound lanes for unknown reasons. A 2009 Toyota and a 2016 Toyota were traveling northbound in the 500 block of S. Pleasant Valley Rd. when the Hyundai crashed head on into the 2009 Toyota. The 2016 Toyota could not stop in time and crashed into the 2009 Toyota. The drivers of both Toyotas were transported to a local hospital with non-life threatening injuries. The driver of the Hyundai was pronounced deceased at the scene.

location: N IH 35 SB frontage road and U.S. 290 EB service road
notes:
Arrested:     Justin Dakota Ayers, White male (26 years of age)

	The preliminary investigation shows that a 2004, white Acura TL was traveling southbound on the N. IH 35 southbound frontage road in the outside lane. The driver of the Acura ran the red light at the U.S. 290 eastbound service road. A 2009 black, Nissan Altima was traveling eastbound on the U.S. 290 eastbound service road in the inside lane. The Altima collided with the front right side of the Acura causing the Acura to then strike a 3rd vehicle, a 2016 white Ford Fusion.

	The female passenger in the Acura was pronounced deceased at the scene. The drivers of the Altima and Fusion were transported to a local hospital with non-life threatening injuries.

	The driver of the Acura, Justin Dakota Ayers, has been arrested and charged with the following:

		intoxication manslaughter

		intoxication assault

		fail to stop and render aid

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2004 green Ford Explorer Sport Trac was traveling eastbound in the 1500 block of E. SH 71. The driver lost control, causing the vehicle to roll. The passenger in the vehicle was pronounced deceased at the scene. The driver of the vehicle was transported to a local hospital with critical injuries.

The preliminary investigation shows that patrol officers were dispatched to the 12200 block of Dessau Rd. in reference to a person down in the roadway. They located a deceased male in the road with obvious traumatic injuries consistent with being struck by a vehicle.

The preliminary investigation shows that a silver, 2011 Toyota Corolla was traveling southbound in the 4200 block of S. Lamar Blvd. when a pedestrian ran in front of the vehicle. The pedestrian was running eastbound across S. Lamar from the Brodie Oaks shopping center, not within the crosswalk. The pedestrian was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas where he died a short time later. 
	The driver of the Toyota Corolla stayed at the scene cooperated. No charges are expected at this time.

The preliminary investigation shows that a pedestrian attempted to cross a high-speed roadway from northbound to southbound. A 2018, red, Dodge Durango was traveling westbound and struck the pedestrian in the roadway. The pedestrian, Ramon Javier Pesina, was pronounced deceased at the scene at 10:41 p.m. The driver of the Durango remained at the scene and there were no signs of impairment.

The preliminary investigation shows that a pedestrian was laying down in the westbound lanes of St. Johns Blvd. for unknown reasons. A Capital Metro bus was heading west on St. Johns Blvd. and was unable to see the pedestrian, Andrew Sanchez, laying in the road. The bus ran Sanchez and he was pronounced deceased at the scene. The driver of the bus stayed at the scene and cooperated.

location: E 290 eastbound service rd. & SH 130 northbound service rd.
notes: The preliminary investigation shows that a 2001 Dodge truck was traveling eastbound on the 290 service road approaching the intersection of the SH 130 northbound service road. The Dodge ran the red light and struck a 2013 Nissan Altima on its left side. An unrestrained, juvenile male, in the back seat of the Nissan, died at the scene.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2009 Freightliner truck and attached trailer was stopped in traffic in the 2500 block of N IH-35, in the left lane, when a 2001 Toyota Avalon struck the back side of the trailer, at a high rate of speed. The driver of the Toyota Avalon was pronounced deceased at the scene.

The preliminary investigation shows that Jonathan Deleon was standing near the rear driver’s side of a parked vehicle in the 2000 block of East Cesar Chavez when a white van or some type of SUV travelling westbound struck him before fleeing. Mr. Deleon was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas where he was pronounced deceased.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2015 Dodge Ram truck was traveling northbound in the 6300 block of IH 35 when the driver struck a pedestrian who was standing in the inside lane. The driver did not see the pedestrian as it was dark at the time of the crash. The pedestrian was pronounced deceased at the scene. The driver stayed on scene and showed no signs of impairment.

location: 12700 block of Research Blvd., frontage rd.
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that a 2013, grey Nissan Altima exited a private drive in the 12700 block of Research Blvd frontage road. The Altima attempted to change lanes into the far left lane. A 2011, grey Ford Escape was traveling southbound in the far left lane of the frontage road. The Altima struck the Escape. The front seat passenger of the Escape, Ronald Hadnot, was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas, but succumbed to his injuries on Tuesday, October 16, 2018. The driver of the Escape was transported to the hospital with non-life-threatening injuries.
	The driver of the Altima remained at the scene and showed no signs of impairment.

location: S SH 130 service road NB and E SH 71 service road WB
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that a silver, 2017 Honda Accord was traveling northbound on SH 130 service road at the intersection of SH 71. A black, 2006 Ford F-250 was traveling westbound at this intersection. The driver of the Honda admitted to running the red light. He was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas where he died at 10:52 p.m. that evening.

	Both drivers remained on scene and intoxication is not suspected to be a factor in this crash.

The preliminary investigation shows that a silver, 2002 Nissan was traveling westbound in FM 1327. A white, 1992 Peterbuilt, tractor trailer, was traveling eastbound in FM 1327. The Nissan drifted to the left and into the eastbound lanes. The tractor/trailer pulled to the right in an attempt to avoid the crash but was struck by the Nissan. The driver of the Nissan was pronounced deceased at the scene.

The preliminary investigation shows that a gold, 2005 Toyota Highlander, was traveling southbound on South Lamar Boulevard, just south of Bluebonnet Lane. There are sidewalks on both sides of S. Lamar and a controlled crosswalk at Bluebonnet Lane.

	For an unknown reason, a pedestrian identified as Seth Mendoza was in the southbound lanes of travel, not in the crosswalk or on the sidewalk. Mendoza was struck by the Toyota Highlander and was pronounced deceased on scene, at 2:32 a.m.

	The driver, who stayed on scene, was identified as 23-year-old William Roy. Roy admitted to drinking and was arrested for DWI. No additional charges are expected at this time.

The preliminary investigation shows that a red, Mazda RX-8 was traveling east bound in the 1200 block of West Oltorf Street at a high rate of speed, when it lost control and struck a tree along the south side of the street.

	The driver of the vehicle, Anthony Zangara, 32, was transported to St. David’s South Austin Medical Center, where he later succumbed to his injuries. Zangara was pronounced deceased on October 30, 2018 at 5:38 p.m.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2017 White, Volvo Truck Tractor was traveling northbound in the 8200 block of N IH-35 NB proper, in the outside lane. A pedestrian, identified as Stefanie Marie Torres, 38, was attempting to cross the highway when the vehicle struck her.

	Torres was pronounced deceased on the scene.

	The truck driver stayed on scene. No charges will be filed at this time.

The preliminary investigation shows that a pedestrian was crossing Manchaca Rd. from the bus stop located at the west curb line to the bus stop located at the east curb line. The area has sidewalks on both sides of Manchaca Rd. but no crosswalk is available at Manchaca and Berkett Dr. The pedestrian was struck by a white, 2014 Nissan that was traveling southbound on Manchaca Rd. when she was crossing.

	The driver of the Nissan stayed at the scene and cooperated. Neither intoxication nor impairment are suspected to be factors in this crash. No charges are expected to be filed at this time.

The preliminary investigation shows that Aaron Ross Weir was standing in the roadway in the 11300 block of N. Mopac when a silver, 2014 Nissan, traveling southbound, struck him.

	Aaron Ross Weir, was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas where he died as a result of his injuries at 3:35 a.m.

	The driver of the Nissan stayed at the scene and cooperated. Neither intoxication nor impairment are suspected to be factors in this crash. No charges are expected to be filed at this time.

The preliminary investigation shows that Brett Lambert was in the roadway near the 1100 block of N IH-35 northbound proper. An unknown vehicle struck Lambert in the early morning of November 4, 2018. The driver left the scene without rendering aid or calling 9-1-1.

	At approximately 6:44 a.m., a passerby contacted 9-1-1 and reported seeing Lambert’s body. Police arrived and located him with obvious trauma, from an apparent auto-pedestrian crash. He was pronounced deceased on scene.

location: 1600 block of E Parmer Lane WB
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that Minh-Tan Pham was biking northbound on Yager Lane when he disregarded posted stop and yield signs and drove across the 1600 block of E Parmer Lane. As Pham began to enter the left lane of westbound traffic, a stretch of roadway with a 60 mph limit, he crossed in front of a blue, 2012 Toyota Camry.

	Minh-Tan Pham was transported by Austin-Travis Count EMS to St. David’s Round Rock Medical Center where he succumbed to his injuries on November 10, 2018. The driver of the Camry remained on scene.

Arrested:       Alan Torres-Yanez, Hispanic male, age 25

	The preliminary investigation shows that Alan Torres-Yanez, age 25, was driving a blue, 2000 Honda westbound on FM 969 when it crashed with a white, Ford van that was attempting to pull out from Regency Drive to go eastbound.

	Yesenia Lopez-Rodriguez, the passenger in the Honda, was transported by Austin-Travis County EMS to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas where she was pronounced deceased at 9:42 p.m. Torres-Yanez was also transported with minor injuries. The driver of the van was uninjured and stayed on scene to cooperate with the investigation.

	Alan Torres-Yanez was arrested for DWI.

The preliminary investigation shows that a black, 2002 Toyota Avalon was traveling northbound near the 14500 block of N 183 A. The driver lost control of the vehicle and crashed into the center cement divider of the highway. The driver and passenger were transported to St. David’s Round Rock Medical Center and the driver later died due to her injuries.

The preliminary investigation shows that Christopher Brown attempted to cross IH-35 on foot from east to west while evading police following a robbery at a nearby convenience store. Mr. Brown jumped over a concrete barrier to cross the heavily-traveled roadway. As he entered the center lane, Brown ran into the rear portion of a passing 18-wheeler. Christopher Brown was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas where he succumbed to his injuries.

	The driver of the 18-wheeler was unaware of the impact and no charges are expected to be filed.

The preliminary investigation shows that Mathew Lutomski was driving a 2008 Subaru southbound on Research Blvd when he exited on to the service road just north of McCann Drive. Lutomski appears to have lost control of the vehicle, striking a metal utility pole on the driver’s side. He was pronounced deceased at the scene.

The preliminary investigation shows that Billy Jack Dickey was struck by a motor vehicle in the 900 block of Springdale Road. Dickey was pronounced deceased at the scene. The driver of the vehicle failed to remain on scene.

location: 183 service road westbound and Payton Gin Rd.
notes: The preliminary investigation shows that a 2004 Honda sedan was traveling northbound on Payton Gin Rd. from a stop. A 2006 Mercedes sedan was traveling westbound on the service road of 183. The Mercedes and the Honda crashed in the intersection. The Honda was damaged on the right side and the Mercedes was damaged on the front end. The driver of the Honda was pronounced deceased at the scene at 8:50 p.m.

The preliminary investigation shows that the 2016 Indian motorcycle driven by Elijah Perales was stopped on the right shoulder of N Mopac SB when an SUV, also traveling southbound, drifted to the right and struck Perales. Perales was pronounced deceased at the scene. The driver of the SUV remained on site. Investigators are still working to determine whether charges will be filed.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2003 Ford F150 was traveling northbound on the US Highway 183 northbound ramp to E. Highway 71, eastbound. The truck went across the E. Highway 71 and US Highway 183 ramp, rolled and came to a stop north of the roadway.
	The passenger was ejected from the vehicle and was pronounced deceased on scene at 2:43 a.m. The driver was transported to St. David’s South Austin Hospital.

The preliminary investigation shows that the victim was walking in a crosswalk from north to south in the 800 block of E. Slaughter Ln. The victim had the right-of-way at the time when a white, 2005 Ford Explorer was traveling westbound on E. Slaughter Ln. approached the intersection of Brandt Rd. The driver of the Explorer entered the intersection against a red light and struck the victim. The driver remained on scene. The victim was transported to the hospital with life-threatening injuries, eventually passing on March 7, 2018 at Dell Children’s Medical Center.

	The case is still being investigated at this time.

location: 3600 block of South Capital of Texas Highway SB
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that the driver of a silver, 2018 KIA was traveling in the center lane of the 3600 block of South Capital of Texas Highway SB when the car collided with Jesus Servantez, a pedestrian in the roadway. The driver remained at the scene and told investigators that he did not see Servantez prior to the crash.

	Jesus Servantez was transported to Saint David’s South Austin Medical Center where he succumbed to his injuries on January 21, 2019. No charges are expected to be filed.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2000 Peterbilt semi truck was travelling southbound in the center lane on IH 35 when it struck pedestrian David Sell. The driver stopped as soon as it was possible to do so and remained on scene. He reported not seeing the pedestrian prior to impact given that it was still dark at the time of the crash. Sell was pronounced deceased at the scene at 6:24 a.m. No charges are expected to be filed.

location: West William Cannon Drive and Ridge Oak Road
notes: The preliminary investigation shows that the grey, 2003 Volkwagen Jetta being driven by Ann Bottenfield-Seago failed to yield at a stop sign while attempting to turn westbound on to West William Cannon Drive from Ridge Oak Road. The Jetta collided with a black, 2017 Chevrolet truck that was eastbound in the inside lane of West William Cannon Drive. Bottenfield-Seago was pronounced deceased at the scene. The passenger in the Jetta and the driver of the truck were both transported to a local hospital with non-life threatening injuries. No charges are expected to be filed.

The preliminary investigation shows that a black, Ford F-150 was traveling southbound on IH-35. A pedestrian, identified as 58-year-old Laura Wray, was traveling eastbound near the 6900 block of N IH-35, when the vehicle struck her. The victim was pronounced deceased at the scene at 01:48 a.m.

location: 500 block N. IH 35 service road southbound
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that a 2006 silver Volkswagen Jetta operated by an Uber driver was traveling southbound in the right lane of N. IH-35 southbound on the service road. The Jetta changed lanes to enter the ramp of southbound IH 35 when it encountered a Lime scooter. The pedestrian on the scooter was traveling the wrong way, northbound in the southbound left lane of the IH-35 service road. The pedestrian was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas. He was pronounced deceased at 2:30 p.m. on Saturday, Feb. 2, 2019. The Uber driver remained on scene and is cooperating as this investigation continues.

	The toxicology results in this case are still pending.

The preliminary investigation shows that the driver of a gray, 2008 Mini Cooper was travelling westbound in the 1000 block of W. Oltorf Street when she lost control and slid into the eastbound path of a gray, 2018 Honda motorcycle. The motorcycle, driven by Trevor Ralston, struck the right side of the Mini Cooper.

	Trevor Ralston was pronounced deceased on scene. The driver of the Mini Cooper remained at the crash location and was cited for failure to control speed.

The preliminary investigation shows that the driver of a 1997, red BMW was traveling northbound in the 6000 block of Springdale Road and lost control. The vehicle skidded sideways before flipping and striking a utility pole.

	The passenger in the vehicle, Messiah Zion Mouton, was pronounced deceased at the scene.

The preliminary investigation shows that two pedestrians were crossing mid-block in the 8100 block of N. Lamar Blvd. when both were struck by an unknown vehicle. One pedestrian had minor injuries and the other was pronounced deceased at the scene. The vehicle that hit them fled and has not been yet identified.

The preliminary investigation shows a silver 2017 Jeep Patriot was traveling eastbound in the 7300 block of E. Riverside Dr. A pedestrian, Rosbel Tamez, was crossing Riverside near Uphill St. when he was struck by the Jeep. Mr. Tamez was transported to St. David’s South Austin Hospital where he died a short time later.

The preliminary investigation shows a white, 2000 Lexus RX300 was traveling eastbound on East 7th Street when the driver ran a red light and struck a grey, 2004 Volkswagen Golf moving northbound on Springdale Road. The force of the impact caused both the Lexus and Volkswagen to also strike a white, 2019 Jeep Cherokee that was stopped at the red light.

	The driver of the Volkswagen Golf, Javier Emanuel Niño Esparza, was pronounced deceased at the scene.

	The driver of the Lexus, Duane Harris, 29, was transported to a local hospital for treatment following the crash as were two other occupants from the vehicle. Harris has been charged with intoxication manslaughter.
 Duane Harris

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2005, silver Nissan Altima was traveling northbound in the 35 block of N IH 35. A pedestrian was attempting to cross IH 35, eastbound, and was struck by the Nissan.

	The driver of the Nissan was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas with minor injuries. The driver showed no signs of impairment and no charges are expected.

	The pedestrian, Earnest Turner, was pronounced deceased on March 30, 2019 at 4:20 p.m.

location: Palo Blanco Ln. and Teri Rd.
notes: The preliminary investigation shows that a 2013, blue Dodge Ram was traveling eastbound on Teri Rd. approaching Palo Blanco Ln. A 2010, gold Toyota Venza was traveling northbound on Palo Blanco, turning left onto Teri Rd. The Ram hit the Venza on the left side. All occupants of the Ram fled on foot. All occupants of the Venza were transported to Dell Children’s Medical Center of Central Texas. The juvenile female, Illianna Martinez, died on March 30, 2019 at 4:26 p.m.

location: 1100 E. Martin Luther King Jr. Blvd.
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that a 2013, white Toyota 4 Runner was traveling westbound on E. MLK Jr. Blvd. in the left lane. Witnesses stated that a bicyclist was traveling eastbound on MLK and crossed over the double yellow lines into the path of the Toyota. The bicyclist, Jessica Rae Saathoff, was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas where she died a short time later.
	The driver of the Toyota remained on scene. No charges are expected to be filed against the driver.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2001, white Chrysler Sebring was traveling northbound in the 7300 block of S. Congress Avenue. Two pedestrians were crossing mid-block in the unlit portion of S. Congress Avenue. The car struck one of the pedestrians and he was pronounced deceased at the scene.

	The driver of the Chrysler remained on scene. No charges are expected to be filed against the driver.

The preliminary investigation indicated that Garrett Davis, the driver of the 2017 Subaru Forester, was traveling eastbound in the 500 block of E. Slaughter Lane when he attempted to turn left and collided with a 1996 Chevrolet truck that was traveling westbound. Mr. Davis was attempting to enter the apartment complex on the south side of the road when he failed to yield right of way. The truck made contact with the passenger side of the Forester, killing both the driver and passenger, Keaton Carnley. There were no other occupants in the Subaru. The driver of the truck suffered minor injuries. All parties were wearing their seatbelts. No charges are expected to be filed.

location: E. Wells Branch Parkway/S. Heatherwilde Boulevard
notes: The preliminary investigation revealed that the 2017 Dodge Charger driven by Hannah Jaggers was traveling eastbound on E. Wells Branch Parkway near the intersection of S. Heatherwilde Boulevard when Ms. Jaggers veered left and struck the curb of the center media, going airborne. The vehicle rolled for several yards before stopping in the intersection. The driver was ejected. Hanna Jaggers was transported to St. David’s Round Rock Medical Center where she succumbed to her injuries on April 4, 2019.

The preliminary investigation revealed that the 2010, blue Honda driven by Wing Chou was travelling eastbound in the 14000 block of N. SH-45 when he lost control and slid into a concrete barrier before rear-ending a parked Austin Fire Department apparatus truck. The AFD vehicle’s emergency lights were activated as it was partially blocking a lane of traffic to help protect a wrecker driver who was loading up a vehicle that had been involved in a separate collision.

	Austin firefighters extracted Mr. Chou and his passenger. They were both transported to St. David’s Round Rock Medical Center where Chou later died from his injuries. The passenger in the vehicle had serious, but not life-threatening injuries. Both occupants were wearing seat belts at the time of the crash.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2014, gray Mitsubishi sedan was traveling southbound in the inside lane of the 11200 block of N. Mopac southbound. The driver of the Mitsubishi stopped to yield right of way to an emergency vehicle when a 2012, white Chevrolet pickup failed to keep assured clear distance and struck the Mitsubishi from behind.

	The driver of the Chevrolet was transported to St. David’s Round Rock Medical Center where he succumbed to his injuries on Tuesday, April 23, 2019 at 6:20 p.m.

The preliminary investigation revealed that a tan, 1998 Chevrolet pickup truck was traveling northbound in the 5600 block of S. Congress Avenue. The truck was in the far right lane, getting ready to move into the turn lane to head east on Stassney Ln. The pedestrian was crossing from westbound to eastbound, mid-block, about 150 feet from a controlled crosswalk. The driver of the truck did not see the pedestrian prior to impact. The pedestrian, James Bourgeois, was pronounced deceased at the scene. The driver remained on scene and there were no signs of impairment.

location: Jollyville Rd. and Balcones Woods Drive.
notes:
The preliminary investigation revealed that a white, 2018 Isuzu conventional truck was traveling northbound in the 1100 block of Jollyville road, approaching the intersection of Balcones Woods Dr. A white, 2015 Cadillac XTS was traveling westbound on Balcones Woods Dr. The Isuzu failed to control speed and entered the intersection striking the Cadillac on the driver’s side. The Isuzu continued across the intersection and struck the front of a gray, 2013 Mazda sedan who was facing south on Jollyville Rd.

	The driver of the Cadillac, Michael Cannatti, was transported to St. David’s Round Rock Medical Center where he died as a result of his injuries.

The preliminary investigation revealed that a 2016, black Toyota 4Runner was exiting a private driveway at 8000 W. Hwy. 290. Signs are posted for right turn only and the driver of the 4Runner failed to comply and made a left turn. A 2008, gray Ford Mustang was traveling westbound in the inside lane and attempted to avoid the 4Runner but struck its front end. The Mustang continued into eastbound lanes of traffic and was struck by a 2013, maroon Dodge Ram.

	The driver of the Mustang was pronounced deceased at the scene.

The preliminary investigation revealed that a 2005, white Chevrolet pickup truck was traveling northbound on FM 973 at the intersection of Pearce Lane when the driver ran a red light and struck the 2001, white Hyundai Elantra that was attempting to turn left on to FM 973 from Pearce Lane. The Chevrolet truck hit the Hyundai on the driver’s side. The driver of the Hyundai was transported to South Austin Hospital where she died a short time later.

The preliminary investigation shows that the deceased, Aric Maxwell, attempted to cross N. IH-35 proper from westbound to eastbound when he was struck by a silver, 2016 Chevy Equinox traveling southbound in the inside lane. Aric Maxwell was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas where he died from his injuries. The driver of the Equinox remained on scene and showed no signs of impairment. No charges are expected to be filed.

location: 8200 block of the Research Boulevard SB Service Road
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that the red, 2013 Ford F-150 driven by Leon Salmeron was traveling southbound in the 8200 block of the Research Boulevard Service Road when the driver of a grey, 2005 Honda Accord failed to yield right of way from a private drive while attempting to exit The Park at Crestview Apartments. The Ford F-150 and Honda collided causing the truck to strike a concrete support column.

	Leon Rogelio Andres Salmeron was pronounced deceased on scene. The driver of the Honda fled the scene on foot. That individual, once identified, will be charged with failure to stop and render aid.

Suspect vehicle description: 
	The preliminary investigation shows that a pedestrian was running from west to east on N. Lamar Blvd. in the 8700 block towards a Capital Metro bus stop. At the time, a Capital Metro bus was present. The pedestrian was struck by a dark colored, small SUV or truck as he was running across Lamar towards the bus stop. The vehicle continued to travel northbound on Lamar and fled the scene. The pedestrian was transported the Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas where he died upon arrival.
	The suspect vehicle possibly has damage to its right, front end.

The preliminary investigation shows Michael Mayes attempted to cross N. I-35 in the 100 block when he was struck by a southbound vehicle traveling in the inside lane. The driver stopped and rendered medical aid immediately. Michael Mayes was transported to a local hospital by Austin-Travis County EMS where he succumbed to his injuries. No charges are expected to be filed.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2018 Hyundai Elantra was traveling southbound in the northbound lanes of IH35. There were 911 calls placed that had APD patrol units in route to the area. Before officers arrived, the calls changed to a head-on crash. A 2008 white Hyundai Elantra hit the Yukon head on.

	The driver of the Elantra, Chiristian Barrios, died at the scene.

	The driver and passenger of the Yukon were transported to an area hospital with non-life threatening injuries. Both occupants of the Yukon were wearing seatbelts.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 1999, tan Toyota Camry was traveling northbound on Mopac Expressway in the 1000 block. For unknown reasons, the driver lost control of the vehicle and slid into a tree in a grassy area between Mopac and the frontage road. Cheyanne Sage Serrano was pronounced deceased at the scene.

The preliminary investigation shows that a tan Hyundai Elantra and a white Toyota Camry were traveling northbound near the 12100 block of N. IH-35. The driver of the Camry tried to take over the lane that the Elantra driver was in and lost control of the vehicle. Both cars slid off the roadway and the Elantra struck a tree. The driver of the Elantra, Patrick Leonard Ervin, died at the scene. The driver of the Camry was transported to a local hospital with non-life threatening injuries.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2011, gray Toyota Corolla was traveling northbound in the right lane in the 1100 block of Airport Blvd. A red, 2013 Kia Soul was traveling southbound on Airport Blvd. and turned left in front of the Corolla. The driver of the Kia was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas and was pronounced deceased at 2:22 a.m. The driver and passenger of the Corolla were transported to an area hospital with non-life threatening injuries.

The preliminary investigation shows that a red, 2014 Honda Civic was traveling northbound in the 14000 block of N. IH-35 NB at approximately 10:54 p.m. on May 18, 2019 when the vehicle struck Cesar Saunders. Saunders was attempting to cross I-35 on foot.

	The driver of the vehicle was transported to an area hospital and was later admitted to ICU. Cesar Saunders was also transported to an area hospital where he died from his injuries at 1:14 a.m.

The preliminary investigation shows that a gray, 2013 Dodge Ram was traveling eastbound on Cumberland Rd. approaching Congress Avenue. Cumberland ends at Congress with a T-intersection. The driver of the Ram, Halbert Hendricks, continued eastbound and impacted a cement barrier. Mr. Hendricks was transported to South Austin Hospital and died as a result of his injuries at 2:01 p.m. He was not wearing a seatbelt.

location: N. Lamar Boulevard and Morrow Street
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that a silver, 2000 Nissan Xterra was traveling southbound on N. Lamar when the driver failed to yield the right of way and attempted to turn left on a flashing yellow light.  A white, 2018 Ford F450 truck that was moving northbound on Lamar proceeded through the intersection on green at which time the vehicles collided.

	The passenger in the Nissan, Luis Fernando Martinez-Vertiz, was transported to a local hospital where he died from his injuries.

	This is an ongoing investigation.

location: Bundyhill Drive and E. Martin Luther King Jr. Boulevard
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that Lance Christopher Smith was driving a blue, 2010 Nissan Altima southbound on Bundyhill when he ran the stop sign at E. Martin Luther King Jr. Boulevard and crashed through a guardrail.

	Lance Smith was pronounced deceased on scene. An autopsy has been performed. The toxicology results are pending.

	This is an ongoing investigation.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2002, silver Mercedes was traveling southbound on IH 35. For unknown reasons, a pedestrian was on the highway. The pedestrian was hit by the Mercedes and died at the scene.

	The driver of the Mercedes remained on scene and cooperated. No charges are expected at this time.

location: 8900 block of N Capital of Texas Highway
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that the driver of a white, 2016 Ford Explorer turned westbound on to N Capital of Texas Highway from Great Hills Trail. She failed to use the dedicated merge lane and moved into the right lane of the roadway, striking the box truck driven by Guadalupe Padilla Palacios. Palacios’ truck was overturned and hit a guard rail.
	Guadalupe Padilla Palacios was transported to a local hospital where he succumbed to his injuries on June 9, 2019.

The preliminary investigation shows that the driver of a silver, 2016 Toyota Tundra was traveling westbound on E Oltorf Street when he took faulty evasive action, moving into the eastbound lane to avoid a vehicle that was stopped in front of him. The driver collided with the oncoming (eastbound) 2015 Harley Davidson motorcycle, driven by 53-year-old Matthew Waters.
	Mr. Waters was transported to a local hospital where he was pronounced deceased.

The preliminary investigation shows that the driver of a 2015 BMW motorcycle was traveling southbound on Webberville Rd. approaching the Springdale Rd. intersection. The motorcycle struck the curb of a small median, which launched the driver from the motorcycle and into the utility pole. The motorcycle came to rest on Springdale Rd. and the driver died at the scene.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2012 Nissan Altima was traveling westbound in the 4600 block of E. Ben White Blvd. and rear-ended a 2007 Chevrolet Tahoe. The passenger of the Nissan was transported to St. David’s South Austin Hospital where she was pronounced deceased at 3:27 a.m.

The preliminary investigation shows that a pedestrian was crossing IH 35 from west to east in the 300 block when a 2007, blue Ford Explorer struck him. The pedestrian was pronounced deceased at the scene.

	The driver of the Explorer remained on scene and was cooperative. No charges are expected at this time.

The preliminary investigation shows that a black Honda CRB motorcycle was traveling eastbound on FM 2222 in the 11000 block when it left the roadway for an unknown reason. The driver of the motorcycle was pronounced deceased on scene.

Casey Ballard was in the 1100 block of S IH-35 NB when a red, 2001 Nissan Frontier pickup that was traveling in the middle lane struck him. He was pronounced deceased on scene. The driver remained on site. There was no sign of driver impairment and no charges are expected to be filed.

The preliminary investigation shows Felix Ybarra was attempting to cross in the 5700 block of S. Congress Avenue, where there is no crosswalk, when he was struck by a maroon, 2013 Kia Sorrento. The driver remained on scene and showed no signs of intoxication.

	Felix Ybarra was transported to Saint David’s South Austin Medical Center where he died on July 30, 2019.

The preliminary investigation shows that a pedestrian was in the roadway for an unknown reason. A 2016 Kenworth tractor/trailer was in the middle lane and struck the pedestrian. The pedestrian was pronounced deceased on scene. The driver remained on scene and was not impaired. No charges are expected to be filed.

The preliminary investigation shows that a pedestrian, Xavier Tunsun, exited a 2016 Chrysler 300 while it was traveling northbound on Cameron Rd. An unknown vehicle struck Tunsun and left the scene northbound on Cameron Rd. The vehicle was possibly gold or tan with dark wheels or no hubcaps. This crash is being investigated as fail to stop and render aid, a 2nd degree felony.

location: U.S. Hwy 290 and William Cannon Dr.
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that Douglas Joseph Vogelsass was walking on William Cannon Dr. northbound across U.S. Highway 290. He disregarded the pedestrian control device and was struck by a 2013 Ford F150.

	Douglas Joseph Vogelsass was pronounced deceased at the scene.

	The driver of the F150 remained on scene and was cooperative. No charges are expected to be filed.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2018, white, Harley Davidson motorcycle was traveling eastbound in the 6600 block of E. Howard Ln. when it struck the inside curb. The motorcycle left the roadway and flipped several times in the center grassy median. The driver of the motorcycle was transported to St. David’s Round Rock Hospital where he was pronounced deceased at 8:32 p.m.

	Excessive speed is not considered to be a factor. The driver was not wearing a helmet.

The preliminary investigation shows that the driver of a black, 2014 Jeep Patriot was traveling eastbound in the inside lane of the 1800 block of W. Parmer Lane when he attempted to take evasive action to stop from striking a Hyundai Veloster that was stopped at the red light at Metric Boulevard. The Jeep clipped the back of the Veloster before jumping the curb of the inside median that divides east and westbound Parmer Lane, striking Derril Glen Lovelace who was standing on the narrow concrete strip. The driver of the Jeep also collided with a silver, 2008 Mitsubishi Lancer and a grey, 2015 Subaru Forester that were traveling westbound on W. Parmer Lane.

	Derril Glen Lovelace was transported to St. David’s Round Rock Medical Center where he was pronounced deceased. The driver of the Subaru Forester was transported to the St. David’s North Austin Medical Center with non-life threatening injuries.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2010, red Chevrolet Tahoe and a 2014, silver Chevrolet Malibu were driving northbound in the 3500 block of Montopolis at a very high rate of speed. The Tahoe hit the back of the Impala and lost control, leaving the roadway. The Tahoe spun and hit bushes on the LCRA property located at 3505 Montopolis Drive. It continued across the parking lot, striking a tree and coming to rest by the loading dock of the building. The back seat passenger, Josephine Guerra, was ejected during the crash and pronounced deceased at the scene at 5:26 a.m. The driver of the Tahoe and two other passengers fled the scene on foot.

	The driver of the Malibu is cooperating with this open and ongoing investigation.

The preliminary investigation yielded testimony from witnesses who reported seeing the BMW motorcycle driven by Cedric Benson traveling at a high rate of speed westbound in the left lane of FM 2222. A white, 2014 Dodge van was stopped at the T-intersection of Mount Bonnell Road and FM 2222. After checking for oncoming traffic, the van attempted to turn left on to FM 2222 when it was struck by the oncoming motorcycle.

	The driver of the van was evaluated by EMS on scene and refused transport. The passenger of the van and a bystander at the scene attempted to render aid to Mr. Benson and his passenger Aamna Najam. Cedric Benson and Aamna Najam were both pronounced on scene.

	The van driver remained on scene and is cooperating with the ongoing investigation.

	The family of Cedric Benson respectfully requests privacy during this difficult time and asks that media refrain from contacting them.

The preliminary investigation indicates that Anthony Ukadibia was leaving the apartment complex located at 515 E. Slaughter Lane in a silver, 2007 Honda Odyssey. As he approached the roadway to make a left, he honked at the vehicle waiting in front of him. When the vehicle didn’t move, Mr. Ukadibia drove around and attempted to cross eastbound Slaughter Lane. He failed to yield right of way and was struck on the driver’s side by an eastbound white, 2000 Mercury 4-door. Anthony Ukadibia, who was not wearing a seatbelt, was ejected from the vehicle and subsequently struck by a 2011 Ford F-150. He was transported to St. David’s South Austin Medical Center by Austin-Travis County EMS where he succumbed to his injuries.

	The drivers of the Mercury and the Ford remained on scene. No charges are expected to be filed.

location: S. IH-35 SB/E. Ben White Blvd. service roads
notes:
The preliminary investigation indicates that Anthony Wayne Washington was riding a bicycle eastbound on the Ben White Blvd. service road when he ran a red light and crossed over into the southbound lanes of the S. IH-35 service road. The driver of a silver, 2017 Chevrolet Cruz was driving in the far left lane of the IH-35 service road when she saw Mr. Washington enter the intersection. She honked to alert him while attempting to stop in time, but he crashed into her vehicle.

	Anthony Wayne Washington was transported to St. David’s South Austin Medical Center where he was pronounced deceased shortly thereafter.

	The driver of the Chevrolet Cruz remained on scene. No charges are expected to be filed.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 1999, blue Pontiac was traveling southbound on the frontage road near the 10200 block of N. IH 35 when it left the roadway for unknown reasons. The vehicle went through a business parking lot and struck a parked vehicle and a pallet of landscaping stones before coming to rest against a business building. The driver was ejected from the vehicle and died at the scene. The front seat passenger was transported to a nearby hospital for treatment.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2005 Suzuki motorcycle was traveling northbound in the 9200 block of Metric Blvd. and a 2018, black Toyota Camry was traveling southbound in the northbound lanes of Metric Blvd. The Camry crashed head-on into the motorcycle. The driver of the motorcycle died at the scene. The driver of the Camry was arrested for DWI and Intoxication Manslaughter.

The preliminary investigation shows that a pedestrian was attempting to cross the 1500 block of N. IH 35 from west to east. A semi tractor-trailer and multiple other vehicles struck the pedestrian. The driver of the tractor-trailer remained on scene and the pedestrian was pronounced deceased at the scene.

The preliminary investigation shows that Louis Chambers was attempting to cross N. IH-35 SB in the 6500 block when he was struck by a green, 2011 Ford Focus that was traveling in the inside lane. Louis Chambers was pronounced deceased on scene.

	The driver of the Ford Focus remained at the crash site and is cooperating with the investigation. No charges are expected to be filed.

The preliminary investigation shows that Jeanny Nunez-Noguera was in the right lane in the 11400 block of N. IH-35 NB proper when he was struck by a red, 2016 Honda Civic.

	The driver of the Honda Civic remained at the crash site and is cooperating with the investigation. No charges are expected to be filed.

location: Hwy 290 WB at the 183 SB Flyover
notes: The preliminary investigation shows Joe H. Ogg was driving a red, 2001 Harley Davidson Motorcycle westbound on Hwy 290 to the southbound 183 flyover when he failed to negotiate the curve and struck a wall with the bike. Joe Ogg went over the wall, falling into the westbound lanes of 290 below. He was pronounced deceased on scene.

location: Hwy 290 WB Service Road at Parmer Lane
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that Scott Remmenga was riding a Honda Silverwing Motorcycle westbound on the 290 service road when the driver of a white, 2016 Toyota Tundra that was traveling parallel to the bike attempted to turn left from the wrong lane, striking Scott Remmenga. He was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas where he died a short time later.

	The driver of the Tundra remained on scene and is cooperating with the investigation.

The preliminary investigation shows that the silver, 2004 Dodge Durango driven by Carlos Asteven Alvarez-Recarte was traveling southbound in the northbound lanes on IH-35 proper when the truck struck a light pole. Carlos Asteven Alvarez-Recarte and the passenger in the vehicle were both transported to an area hospital. Carlos Asteven Alvarez-Recarte succumbed to his injuries on October 4, 2019.

Arrested:      Debrah Callison | White female | 69 years of age
	The preliminary investigation shows that the white, 2018 Toyota RAV-4 driven by Callison was traveling southbound in the outside lane in the 9000 block of S. Congress when she struck Christian Livingson. Mr. Livingston was walking in the roadway rather than on the east curb line sidewalk available to him. He was pronounced deceased at the scene.

	Debrah Callison remained on scene. She was found to be intoxicated and was arrested for DWI. There are no additional charges anticipated at this time.
 Debrah Callison

location: E. Parmer Ln. and Dessau Rd.
notes: The preliminary investigation shows that a 2003 orange Chevrolet Avalanche Pickup truck was traveling eastbound on E. Parmer Ln. and Dessau Rd. at a high rate of speed. A 2019 white Hyundai Elantra was turning left from E. Parmer Ln. onto Southbound Dessau Rd. with a protected green turn signal. The Avalanche ran the red light and struck the Elantra. The Avalanche then struck a metal pole on the Southeast corner of the intersection. The driver of the Avalanche was pronounced deceased on the scene. The driver and passenger of the Elantra were transported to a local hospital with non-life threatening injuries.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2014, maroon Mazda 5 was traveling westbound in the 600 block of E. Yager Ln. A pedestrian was walking westbound in the middle of the road when he was struck by the Mazda. The pedestrian was pronounced deceased on scene.

	The driver of the Mazda remained on scene and cooperated. No charges are expected to be filed at this time.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2007 white, Ford Mustang was stopped in the center lane of southbound IH 35 in the 7400 block. A 2017 white, Peterbuilt Truck Tractor was traveling southbound in the center lane and struck the back of the Mustang. The driver of the Mustang was pronounced deceased on the scene.

	The driver of the Peterbuilt Tractor Truck remained on scene and cooperated. No charges are expected to be filed at this time.

The preliminary investigation shows that a pedestrian was in the middle of the inside lane in the 7200 block of Cameron Rd. A white, 2012 Ford F-150 was heading northbound in the inside lane and struck the pedestrian. The pedestrian was pronounced deceased at the scene. He has been identified as 58-year-old Mauricio Garcia.

location: IH 35 northbound frontage road and Stassney Ln.
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that the driver of a 2005, white Toyota Sienna van was traveling northbound on the frontage road of IH 35, making a left turn onto Stassney Ln. to head westbound. The driver of a 2000, brown Chevrolet van was at the light facing westbound in the inside lane. The driver of a 2014, red Nissan Altima was also facing westbound at the light in the outside lane. The driver of the Chevrolet van and the Nissan Altima said their light turned green and the proceeded through the intersection. The front of the Toyota Sienna van struck the front left of the brown Chevrolet van and then struck the driver side of the Nissan Altima. The Toyota Sienna came to rest on a barrier and had significant front end damage.

	The driver and passenger of the Toyota Sienna were transported to a local hospital with non-life threatening injuries. On October 17, 2019, the passenger in the Toyota Sienna passed away as a result of the injuries sustained in the crash.

location: William Cannon Drive and Emerald Forest Drive
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that the driver of a white, 2015 Ford F250 was traveling westbound in the far right lane on William Cannon Drive while David Tienda was attempting to cross northbound on Emerald Forest Drive against the light in a motorized wheelchair. The truck, which had the green light, proceeded through the intersection and struck David Tienda. He was transported to an area hospital with serious injuries where he died on October 16, 2019.

	The driver of the truck remained on scene. No charges are expected.

location: 13600 West State Highway 45 Eastbound Exit Ramp
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that a 2013, black BMW X6 was traveling eastbound on the State Highway 45 toll road. The vehicle exited in the 13600 block for Parmer Lane and approached the tollbooth. The vehicle left the roadway before reaching the tollbooth, crashed into a barrier wall head-on and caught fire.

	The driver of the BMW was pronounced deceased at the scene.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2015, maroon Hyundai Sonata was traveling southbound on Burnet Rd. in the 10700 block. The vehicle left the roadway to the right, travelled into and out of a drainage ditch and landed upside down. The female passenger was ejected from the vehicle and was pronounced deceased at the scene.

	The driver of the Sonata was transported to a local hospital with serious injuries.

location: 4800 block of N IH 35 southbound service road
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that a 2006, blue Toyota Scion was traveling southbound in the 4800 block of the service road of IH 35 when it left the roadway to the right. The vehicle slid into a wooden utility pole.

	The driver of the Scion was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas where he died a short time later.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2017, white Lexus RX was traveling eastbound on William Cannon Dr. in the middle lane when the driver struck a pedestrian that was attempting to run across the roadway. The pedestrian was not in a crosswalk and was attempting to cross mid-block over six lanes of traffic.

	The driver of the Lexus stayed on scene and is cooperating with the investigation. No charges are expected to be filed at this time.

	The pedestrian was transported to St. David’s South Austin Hospital, but he died on November 13, 2019 as a result of his injuries.

The preliminary investigation indicates a 2003, white Toyota Tundra was traveling eastbound in the 6500 block of Loyola Ln. approaching the intersection of Loyola Ln. and Johnny Morris Rd. A 2003, gray Infiniti was traveling westbound in the 6600 block of Loyola Ln. approaching the same intersection. The Tundra began to turn left onto Johnny Morris Rd. and was t-boned by the Infiniti on the passenger side of the vehicle. All of the people involved in this crash were transported to a local hospital. At the time, it was not believed that any of the injuries were life-threatening, however the passenger in the Tundra died as a result of his injuries on Tuesday, December 3, 2019 at 7:44 p.m.

	The driver of the Infiniti was cited for having no driver’s license.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2017, white Jeep Wrangler was traveling eastbound in the inside lane of E. 51st St. when it struck a pedestrian who was attempting to cross the roadway. The pedestrian, Rachelle Velin Covey, was not within a crosswalk and was attempting to cross five lanes of traffic in an area that is dimly lit. The driver of the vehicle remained on scene and is cooperating with the investigation. No charges are expected to be filed at this time.
The pedestrian was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas where she died later that evening as a result of his injuries.

location: 8200 block of E. US 290 Hwy Svrd EB
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that the white, 2017 Chrysler 200 driven by Damir Hererra Perez was traveling eastbound in the 8200 block of E. US 290 Hwy Svrd at a high rate of speed when it left the roadway for an unknown reason and crashed into a concrete pillar.

	Damir Hererra Perez was pronounced deceased at the scene.

The preliminary investigation shows that the blue, 2009 Kawasaki Ninja motorcycle driven by Matthew James Almasi was traveling northbound in the outside lane of the 5800 block of Burnet Road at a high rate of speed. A gold, 1997 Honda Odyssey minivan was traveling southbound in the inside lane when the driver attempted to make a lefthand turn at which time the minivan and motorcycle collided.

	Matthew James Almasi, who was not wearing a helmet or other personal protective gear, was thrown from his motorcycle. He was transported by Austin-Travis County EMS to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas where he succumbed to his wounds at approximately 8:30 p.m.

	The driver of the minivan, who was uninjured in the crash, remained on scene and has been cooperating with investigators. He was issued a traffic citation for fail to yield right of way – left turn. The passenger in the van was treated at the scene for minor injuries.

location: 800 block of E. William Cannon Drive
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows James Lee Beasley was attempting to cross midblock in the 800 block of E. William Cannon Drive where there is no crosswalk when he was struck by a gold, 2006 Mercury Mariner that was traveling westbound on E. William Cannon and was in the process of a signaled lane change.

	The section of the roadway where James Lee Beasley attempted to cross is heavily congested with vehicular traffic. There is no indication that driver impairment, speed, lighting conditions, or weather/road conditions played a factor.

	Personnel from the Austin Fire Department and Austin-Travis County EMS attempted lifesaving measures, but James Beasley died on scene at approximately 7:38 p.m.

location: 1100 block of E. Ben White Blvd WB
notes:
Arrested:      Amanda Overman, White female, 30 years of age

	The preliminary investigation shows that Amanda Overman was driving a maroon, 2003 Honda CR-V westbound in the 1100 block of E. Ben White Blvd when she lost control of her vehicle and struck the center median. The vehicle ricocheted back into the roadway where it struck Risean Deontay Lee Green and the black and gold, 2009 Yamaha motorcycle he was riding.

	Overman pulled into the shopping center located in the 700 block of E. Ben White Blvd at which time officers made contact with her. Officers conducted a DWI investigation on scene that indicated Amanda Overman was intoxicated.

	Risean Deontay Lee Green was transported to St. David’s South Austin Medical Center with life-threatening injuries. He died there at approximately 7:44 p.m.

	Amanda Overman has been charged with intoxication manslaughter. Her booking photo is below.

Arrested:       Michael Boisse | White male | 45 years of age

	The preliminary investigation indicates that the grey, 2017 Chrysler 300 driven by Michael Boisse was traveling northbound in the 8500 block of S. Congress Avenue when he attempted to turn left into the parking lot of a local business. A black, 2011 Infinity was southbound when the driver struck the 300 on the right-rear passenger side. Mark Evans, 50, was seated behind Michael Boisse and was directly impacted by the crash. Mark Evans was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas with life-threatening injuries where he died a short time later.

	Michael Boisse underwent a standardized field sobriety test on scene. He was arrested and is charged with intoxication manslaughter. His booking photo is below.

The preliminary investigation indicates the grey, 2020 Toyota Camry driven by Cody Allen Faust was traveling eastbound in the 8700 block of W. SH 71 when it crossed into the westbound lanes and struck a white, 2015 Jeep Grand Cherokee head on. Cody Allen Faust was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas where he died at 12:45 p.m.

	The driver of the Jeep Grand Cherokee and the passenger in the Toyota Camry were also transported to an area hospital with non-life threatening injuries.

	An autopsy has been performed. We are awaiting toxicology results to determine whether impairment was a factor.

The preliminary investigation indicates that a white, Freightliner truck towing a white, Great Dane semi-trailer was broken down in the outside shoulder in the 9800 block N. IH 35 NB proper. The black, Ford Edge driven by Allison Hollingshead Banks, for an unknown reason, drove into the rear of the tractor trailer. Allison Hollingshead Banks was transported to St. David’s Round Rock Medical Center where she succumbed to her injuries and was pronounced deceased on 12/9/19 at 11:25 a.m.

The preliminary investigation indicates that a blue and silver Capital Metro bus was traveling westbound near the 2000 block of E. Oltorf. The driver stopped and a few passengers exited the rear door of the bus. The unidentified pedestrian exited the bus and was on the sidewalk. As the bus drove away, the pedestrian stumbled backwards, falling between the curb and the bus. The pedestrian was struck by the back portion of the bus. He was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas and later died as a result of his injuries.

The preliminary investigation shows that a silver, 2014 Dodge Ram pickup was traveling southbound in the 6000 block of Cameron Road at approximately 2:26 a.m. on Monday, December 16, 2019. The truck struck 45-year-old Merry Daye who was in the designated southbound bike lane. Merry Daye was attempting to address a mechanical issue with her bike when she was hit. She was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas where she was pronounced deceased.

	An autopsy has been performed. The official cause of death is pending.

	APD officers located the Dodge Ram that is believed to have been involved. The vehicle was unoccupied. It is currently being processed for evidence.

location: Ben White Frontage Rd. westbound and Congress Avenue
notes: The preliminary investigation shows that a black, 2012 Ford F-150 pickup truck was traveling westbound on the frontage road of Ben White approaching Congress Avenue. The driver of the truck attempted to make the turnaround for the eastbound Ben White frontage road when he lost control and struck the cement barrier. The vehicle caught on fire. The driver was extracted from the truck and transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas where he died as a result of his injuries.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2013, dark blue, Dodge Ram truck was traveling westbound in the 7600 block of SH 71 in the outside lane. The pedestrian was attempting to cross the roadway from the south curb line to the north curb line. The pedestrian was not in a crosswalk and was attempting to cross mid-block over five lanes of traffic in an area that is heavily congested with traffic and not well lit. The driver of the vehicle remained on scene and is cooperating with the investigation. It is not believed that driver impairment, speed, or weather/road conditions were factors in this incident. It is, however, believed that poor lighting conditions in the dark, early-morning hours contributed to the collision. Life-saving measures were attempted on the pedestrian by the Austin Fire Department and Austin-Travis County EMS, but the pedestrian succumbed to her injuries and died on scene at 7:22 a.m.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2008 Toyota Camry was traveling southbound in the 12000 block of Dessau Rd. at the intersection of Braker Ln. when the driver struck a pedestrian in the southbound lanes. Video evidence from the vehicle shows the pedestrian walking across Dessau Rd. from east to west while talking on a cell phone. At the time of the crash, the pedestrian was walking parallel to, but outside of the crosswalk with his head oriented in a downward direction and away from approaching southbound traffic. The pedestrian was pronounced deceased at the scene.

	The driver remained on scene and is cooperating. No charges are expected at this time.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2008 maroon Cadillac was traveling northbound in the right lane of Manor Rd. in the 6700 block. As the vehicle approached the crest of a slight incline, it crashed into a pedestrian who was standing in the middle of the right lane. The pedestrian was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas where he died a short time after arriving. He has not been identified.

	The driver remained on scene and is cooperating. No charges are expected at this time.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2007, grey Toyota Camry was traveling southbound in the 3000-3500 block of S. IH-35 southbound when it left its lane of travel for unknown reasons and struck the concrete barrier dividing the southbound and northbound lanes. The driver was transported to St. David’s South Austin Hospital where she passed away not long after arrival.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2006 BMW BX5 was traveling westbound on Loyola Ln. when it struck a pedestrian who was walking from south to north across the roadway. The elderly pedestrian, along with another family member, were standing in the center median that divides east to westbound lanes of Loyola Ln. The pedestrian began to walk across Loyola Ln. and was struck in the middle of the roadway. The driver of the BMW remained on scene and cooperated with the investigation. No charges are expected at this time.

	The pedestrian was pronounced deceased on scene.

The preliminary investigation shows that a 2014, silver Ford Focus was traveling northbound in the inside lane of the 1100 block of Airport Blvd. The Focus struck a pedestrian who was crossing Airport Blvd. from the west to east curb line. A 2020, blue Toyota Tacoma was traveling behind the Focus and also struck the pedestrian while he was laying in the roadway.

	Both drivers remained on scene and are cooperating with the investigation. Driver impairment is not believed to be a factor in this auto-pedestrian collision and no charges are expected at this time.
	The pedestrian was pronounced deceased on scene. It is believed the pedestrian may have been impaired.

location: 12600 block of N. Mopac Expressway SB
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that Leon Jay Harvey was driving a white, 2015 Toyota Prius in the right lane in the 12600 block of N. Mopac Expressway SB when he attempted to take the exit and struck a barrier. The impact of the crash caused the vehicle to re-enter the roadway, putting it in the path of a black, 2013 Ford F150 that collided with the passenger’s side of the Prius.

	The driver of the Ford was uninjured and remained on scene. Leon Jay Harvey was pronounced deceased on site. Speed is believed to have been a factor in the crash. There are no charges expected.

The preliminary investigation shows that a silver, 2012 Chevrolet truck and a red, 2005, Infinity sedan were in the parking lot near the 7600 block of Bluff Springs Rd. when they decided to have a road race. The Chevrolet truck and the Infiniti drove south near the 8200 block of Bluff Springs Rd. to start the race. The Chevrolet truck was in the left lane and the Infiniti was in the right lanes of northbound Bluff Springs Rd. As they raced, the Infiniti pulled way ahead of the Chevrolet truck. As the Infiniti approached the 7600 block of Bluff Springs Rd., the Infiniti attempted to turn left into the parking lot where they had previously been sitting. The Chevrolet truck hit the driver’s side of the Infiniti as it was attempting the turn. The Infiniti spun several times and came to final rest against a pole on the west side of the roadway. The driver of the Infiniti was transported to St. David’s South Austin Hospital where he died as a result of his injuries at 12:18 a.m. on Thursday, January 16, 2020. The driver of the Chevrolet truck initially fled the scene after the crash but returned to the scene later.
	Jorge Luis Lopez-Dominguez was arrested and has been charged with two second degree felonies, racing on a highway and fail to stop and render aid. His total bond amount is $100,000.

The preliminary investigation shows Mario Estrada was driving a red, 2015 Dodge Charger northbound on SH 130 when he lost control and left the roadway, coming to rest against a concrete bridge support in the center median. Mario Estrada was pronounced deceased on scene. He was wearing his seatbelt.

The preliminary investigation shows that the driver of a grey, 2005 Ford F-150 was traveling westbound in the 4700 block of Burleson Road when two pedestrians walked into the path of the oncoming vehicle. Juan Palacios, one of the pedestrians, was struck. He was transported to Saint David’s South Austin Medical Center where he died on January 26, 2020.

	The area where Juan Palacios and his companion were crossing was dark and there are no crosswalks in the area. No charges are expected to be filed in this case.

The preliminary investigation shows that D’Avion Lee Suon was driving a grey, 2007 Toyota Corolla eastbound in the 1400 block of W. Cesar Chavez. She crossed the center line into the oncoming path of a green, 1993 Chevrolet Silverado and the two vehicles collided. 

	D’Avion Lee Suon was pronounced deceased at the scene. She was wearing her seatbelt. The driver of the Chevrolet Silverado was transported to an area hospital with non-life threatening injuries.

The preliminary investigation shows that Mitchell Jacob Levy was approaching the 1600 block of W. Howard Lane on his black, 2016 Yamaha Motorcycle from the east when he lost control just prior to the Howard Lane/Metric Boulevard intersection. He slid into the path of a westbound white, 2016 Ford Explorer that was attempting to turn southbound on to Metric Boulevard. The impact of the crash caused the Ford Explorer to roll on its side.

	Mitchell Jacob Levy was pronounced deceased on scene. The driver of the Ford Explorer, Lisa Lene Aiken, was transported to Dell Seton Medical Center at The University of Texas for non-life threatening injuries. She was subsequently arrested for driving while intoxicated. Her intoxication does not appear to have caused the crash.

The preliminary investigation shows that a gray, 2006, Honda Accord was traveling eastbound in the 5800 block of Southwest Parkway where it appears to have lost control. The vehicle left the roadway and crashed into a tree located on the south curb line. The driver of the vehicle was pronounced deceased at the scene at 2:45 p.m.

location: Collinfield Dr. and W. Rundberg Ln.
notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that this was a five-vehicle crash. The signal lights at the intersection of W. Rundberg Ln. and Collinfield Dr. were inoperable due to a power outage in the area. A 2013 Chevrolet Silverado was traveling eastbound in the 1100 block of Rundberg Ln. approaching the intersection of W. Rundberg Ln. and Collinfield Dr. A 1999 Toyota Camry was traveling southbound in the 1000 block of Mearns Meadow Blvd., preparing to turn eastbound onto the 1000 block of W. Rundberg Ln. A 2015 Buick LaCrosse was traveling northbound in the 9300 block of Collinfield Dr. approaching the intersection with W. Rundberg Ln. A 2004 Ford Expedition was stopped facing westbound at the intersection of W. Rundberg Ln. and Collinfield Dr. as a 2018 Ford Mustang was pulling up behind the Mustang, preparing to stop.

	The Chevrolet Silverado, Toyota Camry and Buick LaCrosse entered the intersection at the same time. The Chevrolet Silverado collided into the driver’s side of the Buick LaCrosse and into the front of the Toyota Camry. Debris from the crash damaged the Ford Expedition and after the initial crash, the Buick Lacrosse collided into the Ford Mustang.

	Two of the occupants of the Chevrolet Silverado and two of the occupants of the Toyota Camry were transported to a local hospital with non-life-threatening injuries. The driver of the Buick LaCrosse was transported to Dell-Seton Medical Center at the University of Texas where he died as a result of his injuries at 10:54 a.m.

	It is not believed that driver impairment, weather or road conditions were factors in the crash. The cause of the power outage for the signal lights is unknown at this time but is believed to be a contributing factor in the crash.

	APD would like to remind the public to treat any intersection with signal outages as a 4-way stop.

The preliminary investigation shows that the black, 2007 Mitsubishi Eclipse in which Vincent Laroy Cleveland was a passenger was traveling eastbound in the inside lane in the 1200 block of E. Rundberg Lane when the driver attempted to turn left onto northbound Teasdale Terrace. A white, 2007 Ford F150 moving westbound on Rundberg collided with the passenger’s side of the Mitsubishi.

	Vincent Laroy Cleveland was transported to Ascension Seton Medical Center Austin following the crash where he died on February 10, 2020 at 3:50 p.m. as a result of his injuries. Based on information gathered during the ongoing investigation, it does not appear that driver impairment or speed were factors in the crash. All parties remained on scene and cooperated.

location: North Capital of Texas Hwy/North Mopac NB Svrd

notes:
The preliminary investigation shows that a 2005, red Honda Accord was exiting a private drive in the 7800 block of FM 969 and attempting to turn westbound onto FM 969. A 2020, silver Chevrolet Equinox was traveling eastbound in the outside lane of FM 969 and struck the driver’s side with its front.
